ment shall notify such inmates that they may post their own bail.\\lang1033  Within such time period, the department shall\\highlight0\\lang9 , to the extent practicable and in a manner consistent with officer safety and all applicable laws, offer such inmates the opportunity to obtain property, including personal contact information and financial resources, that such inmates may require for the purpose of posting bail and which is stored in such inmate\\rquote s personal property, provided that any member of the department who accesses such inmate\\rquote s property pursuant to this subdivision shall request access only for the purpose of facilitating posting bail. \\highlight1\\par\nc. The department shall ensure that bail facilitators meet with all eligible inmates within 48 hours of their admission to the custody of the department, that eligible inmates have continued access to bail facilitators, and that bail facilitators are provided with reasonable resources necessary to fulfill their duties.\\par\n\\cf2\\ulnone\\'a7 2. This local law takes effect 180 days after it becomes law.\\par\n\\pard\\ltrpar\\tx916\\tx1832\\tx2748\\tx3664\\tx4580\\tx5496\\tx6412\\tx7328\\tx8244\\tx9160\\tx10076\\tx10992\\tx11908\\tx12824\\tx13740\\tx14656\\highlight0\\fs20 LS #8979\\par\n\\pard\\ltrpar\\highlight1 BC\\par\n5/26/17 6:19 PM\\par\n\\pard\\ltrpar\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\cf0\\highlight0\\fs24\\par\n\\pard\\ltrpar\\fi720\\sl480\\slmult1\\fs22\\par\n\\pard\\ltrpar\\sa160\\sl252\\slmult1\\lang1033\\par\n\\par\n}\n",
